{
  "texts": [
    "There are generally three methods for constructing datasets for model training.",
    "The first method involves guiding a LLM to output instructions that meet expectations.",
    "Typically, the LLM is given a certain identity (e.g., an expert question setter), along with requirements and examples for instruction generation.",
    "This allows the model to follow rules in answering questions or generating new instruction samples.",
    "Self-Instruct (Wang et al, 2023f) is a framework that sets initial instructions, automatically generates instruction samples, and iteratively filters them."
  ]
}